@{
    ViewBag.Title = "MyGarden";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}
<head>
    <title></title>
    <style>
        * {
            -webkit-box-sizing: border-box; /* Safari/Chrome, other WebKit */
            -moz-box-sizing: border-box; /* Firefox, other Gecko */
            box-sizing: border-box; /* Opera/IE 8+ */
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
        }

        .center {
            margin: 0px auto;
        }


        .row .col.l4 {
            width: 245px;
            margin-left: 5px;
        }

        .card {
            padding-top: 11px;
        }

            .card .card-image {
                padding-top: 11px;
            }

        .btn-floating {
            text-transform: lowercase;
        }

        .card .card-title {
            font-size: 14px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<div class="container" data-ng-controller="gardenController as garden" id="PlantControllerElement">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col s12 m12 l12"><h3>My Garden</h3></div>
        <div class="col s6 m4 l2"><a class="btn-floating btn-large waves-effect waves-light red"><i>add</i></a></div>

    </div>
    <!--Card Reveals-->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="center card col s12 m4 l4">
            <div class="card-image waves-effect waves-block waves-light">
                <img class="activator" ng-src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ee/Flame_Azalea_Rhododendron_calendulaceum_%27Mandarin_Red%27_Leaf_Closeup_3264px.jpg/800px-Flame_Azalea_Rhododendron_calendulaceum_%27Mandarin_Red%27_Leaf_Closeup_3264px.jpg">
            </div>
            <div class=" activator card-content">
                <span class="card-title grey-text text-darken-4">Flame Azalea<i class="mdi-navigation-more-vert right"></i></span>
                <p><a href="#">Unplant</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-reveal">
                <span class="card-title grey-text text-darken-4">Watering<i class="mdi-navigation-close right"></i></span>
                <p>Flame azalea prefers moist soil but never soggy, waterlogged soil. This is why well-draining soil is so important. Water flame azalea generously when the top of the soil feels slightly dry, wetting the soil to a depth of 8 to 12 inches. Avoid overhead watering, and keep the foliage as dry as possible. Watering at the base of the plant with a garden hose or soaker is best, because this azalea is susceptible to fungal and bacterial diseases in humid conditions. Proper watering, adequate air circulation and a neat, tidy garden help prevent moisture-related diseases.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="center card col s12 m4 l4">
            <div class="card-image waves-effect waves-block waves-light">
                <img class="activator" ng-src="http://128.253.192.70/users/dws/12_10_06/EriogonumArborescens/EriogonumArborescens3.JPG">
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
                <span class="card-title activator grey-text text-darken-4">Santa Cruz Island buckwheat (Eriogonum arborescens)<i class="mdi-navigation-more-vert right"></i></span>
                <p><a href="#">Unplant</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-reveal">
                <span class="card-title grey-text text-darken-4">Watering<i class="mdi-navigation-close right"></i></span>
                <p>Here is some more information about this product that is only revealed once clicked on.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="center card col s12 m4 l4">
            <div class="card-image waves-effect waves-block waves-light">
                <img class="activator" ng-src="http://plants.usda.gov/gallery/large/meli7_001_lhp.jpg">
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
                <span class="card-title activator grey-text text-darken-4">Snow in Summer (Melaleuca linariifolia)<i class="mdi-navigation-more-vert right"></i></span>
                <p><a href="#">Unplant</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-reveal">
                <span class="card-title grey-text text-darken-4">Watering<i class="mdi-navigation-close right"></i></span>
                <p>Here is some more information about this product that is only revealed once clicked on.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="card col s12 m4 l4">
            <div class="card-image waves-effect waves-block waves-light">
                <img class="activator" ng-src="http://www.hydrangeashydrangeas.com/images/Identify/mac_mop_leaf.jpg">
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
                <span class="card-title activator grey-text text-darken-4"> Mophead (Hydrangea Macrophylla)<i class="mdi-navigation-more-vert right"></i></span>
                <p><a href="#">Unplant</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-reveal">
                <span class="card-title grey-text text-darken-4">Watering<i class="mdi-navigation-close right"></i></span>
                <p>Here is some more information about this product that is only revealed once clicked on.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card col s12 m4 l4">
            <div class="card-image waves-effect waves-block waves-light">
                <img class="activator" ng-src="http://www.herbalteasonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Mulberry-Leaf.jpg">
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
                <span class="card-title activator grey-text text-darken-4">Mullberry<i class="mdi-navigation-more-vert right"></i></span>
                <p><a href="#">Unplant</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-reveal">
                <span class="card-title grey-text text-darken-4">Watering<i class="mdi-navigation-close right"></i></span>
                <p>Here is some more information about this product that is only revealed once clicked on.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card col s12 m4 l4">
